mixed vegetables, reserved parsley stalks and 1 tsp salt in mixing bowl. Set Varoma in position and cook <b>30 min\/Varoma\/\/speed <b>. Remove Varoma and transfer bread dumplings to individual soup bowls. Strain broth through a fine mesh strainer over dumplings. Serve hot with reserved grated Parmesan cheese on the side."}],"hintsAndTricks":["The quintessential comfort food, chicken broth with dumplings is a perfect way to ward off winter chills or to enjoy as a light spring or summer lunch. The dumplings can be served with other soups too, or on their own as a side dish – they’re perfect for soaking up sauces.","Dry rolls or white bread should be at least one day old but not completely hard.","After straining the broth in <b>step 7,<b> allow chicken wings to cool for a few minutes, then pick the meat off the bones with the aid of a fork, discarding the skin, and add chicken meat to soup bowls or save it for another use.","The broth has a delicate chicken flavour. For a stronger broth, feel free to add extra vegetables or meat in <b>step 7<b> (e.g. chicken, beef, veal).","For an even easier version, replace chicken wings with <b>2 heaped<b> tsp homemade chicken stock paste or <b>2 chicken<b> stock cubes (each for <b>0.5 l).<b>","Add <b>120 g<b> bacon cubes or diced ham to dumplings in <b>step 4.<b>"],"basicInfo":["medium","35m","1h 5m","4 portions"]}